---
/**
 * ArchTab3AttributeNaming — Tab 3 of the System Architecture page.
 *
 * Contains the "Attribute Naming" Architecture Decision Record:
 * - Hero section (attribute variant)
 * - The Problem / The Rule split section
 * - Wrong vs Correct code comparison
 * - Allowed vs Must-prefix classification
 * - Cross-platform safety matrix
 * - Recommendation section
 */
---

<div id="tab-attributes" class="da-tab-content" role="tabpanel">
  <section class="da-hero da-hero-attributes" aria-label="Attribute Naming Convention Decision">
    <div class="da-hero-grid" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="da-hero-orb da-hero-orb-1" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="da-hero-orb da-hero-orb-2" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="da-hero-orb da-hero-orb-3" aria-hidden="true"></div>

    <div class="da-hero-content">
      <div class="da-hero-badge">
        <span class="da-hero-badge-dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        Architecture Decision Record
      </div>

      <h1 class="da-hero-title">The Attribute That<br />Breaks Everything</h1>

      <p class="da-hero-subtitle">How a Single Attribute Name Causes Silent Failures</p>

      <p class="da-hero-description">
        When a custom element uses an attribute name that matches a standard HTML attribute,
        CMS preprocessors, framework compilers, and browser parsers may intercept, rewrite,
        or strip it <strong>before</strong> your web component ever receives it. The result:
        <strong>silent failures</strong> that are nearly impossible to debug in production.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mouse-scroll-wrap mouse-scroll-wrap--absolute" aria-hidden="true">
      <div class="mouse-scroll-body"><div class="mouse-scroll-wheel"></div></div>
      <span class="mouse-scroll-label">Scroll</span>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- THE PROBLEM & THE RULE -->
  <section class="da-section" aria-label="The problem and the rule">
    <div class="da-section-inner">
      <div class="da-section-header scroll-reveal">
        <span class="da-section-label">The Core Issue</span>
        <h2 class="da-section-title">Invisible Collisions</h2>
        <p class="da-section-description">
          Standard HTML attributes carry semantic meaning. When custom elements reuse
          those names, entire layers of the web stack fight over control.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="da-attr-split">
        <div class="da-attr-problem scroll-reveal scroll-reveal-delay-1">
          <div class="da-attr-icon-wrap da-attr-icon-danger" aria-hidden="true">
            <i class="fa-solid fa-explosion"></i>
          </div>
          <h3 class="da-attr-heading">The Problem</h3>
          <p class="da-attr-text">
            When a custom element uses an attribute name that matches a standard HTML attribute
            &mdash; like <strong>href</strong>, <strong>src</strong>, <strong>action</strong>,
            <strong>target</strong>, <strong>method</strong>, <strong>role</strong>,
            <strong>for</strong>, or <strong>data</strong> &mdash;
            CMS preprocessors (Drupal, WordPress), framework compilers (React, Vue, Angular),
            and browser HTML parsers may intercept, rewrite, or strip these attributes
            before the web component receives them.
          </p>
          <p class="da-attr-text" style="margin-top: var(--space-4);">
            This causes <strong>silent failures</strong> that are extremely difficult to debug.
            The component renders, but the data never arrives. No error is thrown. No warning
            appears in the console. The attribute simply vanishes.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="da-attr-rule scroll-reveal scroll-reveal-delay-2">
          <div class="da-attr-icon-wrap da-attr-icon-safe" aria-hidden="true">
            <i class="fa-solid fa-shield-halved"></i>
          </div>
          <h3 class="da-attr-heading">The Rule</h3>
          <p class="da-attr-text">
            Any attribute that does <strong>NOT</strong> mirror standard HTMLElement behavior
            must be prefixed with <strong>hx-</strong>. This ensures zero conflict with any
            current or future HTML specification attribute.
          </p>
          <p class="da-attr-text" style="margin-top: var(--space-4);">
            The prefix acts as a <strong>namespace</strong>, clearly signaling to every layer
            of the stack &mdash; browsers, CMS engines, bundlers, and frameworks &mdash; that
            this attribute belongs exclusively to the web component and should be passed
            through without modification.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Code Comparison: Wrong vs Correct -->
      <div class="da-section-header scroll-reveal">
        <span class="da-section-label">In Practice</span>
        <h2 class="da-section-title">Wrong vs. Correct</h2>
        <p class="da-section-description">
          A single prefix makes the difference between a component that works
          everywhere and one that silently fails in production.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="da-attr-code-compare scroll-reveal scroll-reveal-delay-1">
        <div class="da-attr-code-col">
          <span class="da-attr-code-label da-attr-code-label-wrong">
            <i class="fa-solid fa-xmark" aria-hidden="true"></i>
            Dangerous &mdash; Attribute Collision
          </span>
          <div class="da-code-block">
            <div class="da-code-titlebar">
              <span class="da-code-dot"></span>
              <span class="da-code-dot"></span>
              <span class="da-code-dot"></span>
              <span class="da-code-filename">card.html.twig</span>
            </div>
            <div class="da-code-body">
              <pre><span class="cmt">&#123;# DANGER: href collides with HTML spec #&#125;</span>
&lt;<span class="tag">hx-card</span>
  <span class="prop-hl">href</span>=<span class="val">"/article/&#123;&#123; nid &#125;&#125;"</span>
  <span class="prop-hl">target</span>=<span class="val">"_blank"</span>
&gt;
  &lt;<span class="tag">h3</span> <span class="slot-hl">slot="heading"</span>&gt;&#123;&#123; title &#125;&#125;&lt;/<span class="tag">h3</span>&gt;
&lt;/<span class="tag">hx-card</span>&gt;</pre>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="da-attr-code-caption">
            <strong>Drupal's link preprocessor intercepts <code>href</code></strong> and
            attempts to resolve it as a route. The attribute may be rewritten, stripped,
            or cause a Twig rendering error.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="da-attr-code-col">
          <span class="da-attr-code-label da-attr-code-label-correct">
            <i class="fa-solid fa-check" aria-hidden="true"></i>
            Safe &mdash; Prefixed Attribute
          </span>
          <div class="da-code-block">
            <div class="da-code-titlebar">
              <span class="da-code-dot"></span>
              <span class="da-code-dot"></span>
              <span class="da-code-dot"></span>
              <span class="da-code-filename">card.html.twig</span>
            </div>
            <div class="da-code-body">
              <pre><span class="cmt">&#123;# SAFE: hx- prefix avoids all collisions #&#125;</span>
&lt;<span class="tag">hx-card</span>
  <span class="prop-hl">hx-href</span>=<span class="val">"/article/&#123;&#123; nid &#125;&#125;"</span>
  <span class="prop-hl">hx-target</span>=<span class="val">"_blank"</span>
&gt;
  &lt;<span class="tag">h3</span> <span class="slot-hl">slot="heading"</span>&gt;&#123;&#123; title &#125;&#125;&lt;/<span class="tag">h3</span>&gt;
&lt;/<span class="tag">hx-card</span>&gt;</pre>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="da-attr-code-caption is-safe">
            <strong>No CMS preprocessor touches <code>hx-href</code></strong>. The attribute
            passes through every layer untouched and arrives safely at the web component.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ALLOWED vs MUST-PREFIX -->
  <section class="da-section" style="border-top: 1px solid var(--surface-3);" aria-label="Attribute classification">
    <div class="da-section-inner">
      <div class="da-section-header scroll-reveal">
        <span class="da-section-label">Classification</span>
        <h2 class="da-section-title">Safe vs. Dangerous</h2>
        <p class="da-section-description">
          Some attributes mirror native HTML behavior and are expected by browsers.
          Others will collide with the platform if used directly.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="da-attr-lists">
        <div class="da-attr-list-card scroll-reveal scroll-reveal-delay-1">
          <div class="da-attr-list-header">
            <div class="da-attr-list-icon da-attr-list-icon-safe" aria-hidden="true">
              <i class="fa-solid fa-lock-open"></i>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="da-attr-list-title">Allowed Without Prefix</div>
              <div class="da-attr-list-desc">Mirrors native HTML behavior</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="da-attr-tags">
            <span class="da-attr-tag da-attr-tag-safe">disabled</span>
            <span class="da-attr-tag da-attr-tag-safe">required</span>
            <span class="da-attr-tag da-attr-tag-safe">name</span>
            <span class="da-attr-tag da-attr-tag-safe">value</span>
            <span class="da-attr-tag da-attr-tag-safe">type</span>
            <span class="da-attr-tag da-attr-tag-safe">placeholder</span>
            <span class="da-attr-tag da-attr-tag-safe">hidden</span>
            <span class="da-attr-tag da-attr-tag-safe">tabindex</span>
          </div>
          <p class="da-attr-list-note">
            These attributes mirror behavior that browsers and frameworks expect on
            form-associated and interactive elements. Using them without a prefix ensures
            compatibility with native form participation, accessibility APIs, and
            framework bindings.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="da-attr-list-card scroll-reveal scroll-reveal-delay-2">
          <div class="da-attr-list-header">
            <div class="da-attr-list-icon da-attr-list-icon-prefix" aria-hidden="true">
              <i class="fa-solid fa-lock"></i>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="da-attr-list-title">Must Use hx- Prefix</div>
              <div class="da-attr-list-desc">Would conflict with HTML/CMS/frameworks</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="da-attr-tags">
            <span class="da-attr-tag da-attr-tag-danger">href</span>
            <span class="da-attr-tag-arrow" aria-hidden="true"><i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-right"></i></span>
            <span class="da-attr-tag da-attr-tag-result">hx-href</span>

            <span class="da-attr-tag da-attr-tag-danger">src</span>
            <span class="da-attr-tag-arrow" aria-hidden="true"><i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-right"></i></span>
            <span class="da-attr-tag da-attr-tag-result">hx-src</span>

            <span class="da-attr-tag da-attr-tag-danger">action</span>
            <span class="da-attr-tag-arrow" aria-hidden="true"><i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-right"></i></span>
            <span class="da-attr-tag da-attr-tag-result">hx-action</span>

            <span class="da-attr-tag da-attr-tag-danger">target</span>
            <span class="da-attr-tag-arrow" aria-hidden="true"><i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-right"></i></span>
            <span class="da-attr-tag da-attr-tag-result">hx-target</span>

            <span class="da-attr-tag da-attr-tag-danger">method</span>
            <span class="da-attr-tag-arrow" aria-hidden="true"><i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-right"></i></span>
            <span class="da-attr-tag da-attr-tag-result">hx-method</span>

            <span class="da-attr-tag da-attr-tag-danger">role</span>
            <span class="da-attr-tag-arrow" aria-hidden="true"><i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-right"></i></span>
            <span class="da-attr-tag da-attr-tag-result">hx-role</span>

            <span class="da-attr-tag da-attr-tag-danger">for</span>
            <span class="da-attr-tag-arrow" aria-hidden="true"><i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-right"></i></span>
            <span class="da-attr-tag da-attr-tag-result">hx-for</span>

            <span class="da-attr-tag da-attr-tag-danger">data</span>
            <span class="da-attr-tag-arrow" aria-hidden="true"><i class="fa-solid fa-arrow-right"></i></span>
            <span class="da-attr-tag da-attr-tag-result">hx-data</span>
          </div>
          <p class="da-attr-list-note">
            These attribute names have established meaning in HTML, ARIA, or CMS
            template engines. Using them directly on custom elements causes preprocessors,
            compilers, and parsers to intercept and modify them before the web component
            ever sees the value.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- DECISION MATRIX -->
  <section class="da-section" style="border-top: 1px solid var(--surface-3);" aria-label="Attribute safety matrix">
